## FAQ

**Q: Can I use prATC for my company's internal PR management?**

A: No, that would be a Commercial Purpose. You need a commercial license. Contact us at jefferson@heimdallstrategy.com.

**Q: Can I use prATC for my open source project?**

A: Yes! Non-commercial open source projects are permitted under this license.

**Q: Can I host prATC as a service?**

A: No, that would be a Commercial Purpose. You need a commercial license.

**Q: When does prATC become Apache 2.0 licensed?**

A: Two years after the first public release under FSL-1.1-Apache-2.0. After that date, anyone can use it for any purpose under Apache 2.0 terms.

**Q: Can I contribute to prATC?**

A: Yes! We welcome contributions. By contributing, you agree that your contributions are licensed under the same FSL-1.1-Apache-2.0 license.
